symposium.model

Interface Range

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<Range>, java.lang.Iterable<TimeRange>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    TimeRange, TimeRangeSeries

    public interface Range
extends java.lang.Comparable<Range>, java.lang.Iterable<TimeRange>
    An interface for absolute ranges. Range is inclusive, i.e [1,2] includes 1 and 2. Therefore, we can have range with same start and end. it will be of length 1.

      • compareTo

        int compareTo(Range other)
        compare two ranges. ranges are compared by their start and end time. A > B if (A.start > B.start) or (A.start == B.start and A.end > B.end)
        Specified by:
        compareTo in interface java.lang.Comparable<Range>
